🟢 EASY (Basic Loop Practice)
Print numbers from 1 to N.*
Print the sum of first N natural numbers.*
Print the factorial of a number.*
Reverse a given number (e.g., 123 → 321).*
Count the number of digits in a number.*
Print multiplication table of N.*
Print all even numbers up to N.*
Find the sum of digits of a number.*
Find the product of digits of a number.*
Check if a number is palindrome.*


🟡 MEDIUM (Conditions Inside Loops)
Check if a number is prime.
Print all prime numbers up to N.
Print Fibonacci series up to N terms.
Find the GCD (HCF) of two numbers using loops.
Find the LCM of two numbers using loops.
Count vowels and consonants in a string using loops.
Check if a number is Armstrong (e.g., 153 = 1³ + 5³ + 3³).
Check if a number is Perfect (e.g., 28 = 1 + 2 + 4 + 7 + 14).
Find the smallest digit in a number.
Find the largest digit in a number.
Calculate power of a number (a^b) using loops.
Find sum of squares of first N natural numbers.


🔴 HARD (Complex Looping Logic)
Print all factors of a number.
Find all prime factors of a number.
Find the largest prime factor of a number.
Find the GCD of an array of numbers using loops.
Find the LCM of an array of numbers using loops.
Find the largest palindrome number in a given range.
Print first N numbers that are both prime and palindrome.
Generate Pascal’s Triangle (first N rows) using loops.